  "texts": [
    "However, the model tends to misclassify negative \"-1\" and positive \"1\" emotions as \"0\", with misclassifications of \"-1\" being notably frequent.",
    "Figure 4b for the 5-class classification illustrates a decline in discrimination ability as the number of categories increases.",
    "Although predictions for the \"0\" category remain relatively accurate, errors for other emotional categories rise, particularly for \"-1\" and \"1\".",
    "Figure 4c for the 7-class classification further demonstrates a decrease in classification performance with an increase in category count.",
    "In this more complex classification task, the model struggles to discern subtler emotional differences, especially around the neutral category.Figure 5a presents the 3-class confusion matrix, where the horizontal axis represents predicted labels and the vertical axis denotes true labels, with positive \"1\", negative \"-1\", and neutral \"0\" emotions."
